  <head>
    <title>Savannah &amp; ftp</title>
    <abstract>
      <para>Slow connection or ftp site down?  We have a collection of
      alternative ftp mirrors as well as a CD-ROM.</para>
    </abstract>
  </head>

  <simplesect id="release-ftp">
    <title>Mirrors</title>

    <para>ftp mirrors for
      <filename>&ftproot;</filename> (source, apps, and
      docs, packages):
    </para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para><ulink
                       url="ftp://ftp.ccp14.dl.ac.uk/ccp14/ftp-mirror/alife/swarm/pub/swarm/">European
                       Mirror</ulink></para>
      </listitem>
        <listitem>
        <para><ulink
          url="ftp://mirror.aarnet.edu.au/pub/swarm">Australian
          Mirror</ulink> Australian Academic and Research Network
          (AARNET) <emphasis>accessible within Australian
          <literal>.au</literal> and New Zealand
          <literal>.nz</literal>domains only</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
          
      <listitem>
        <para><ulink url="ftp://ftp.nr.usu.edu/pub/swarm">Utah State
          University</ulink> <emphasis> (thanks to <ulink
          url="mailto:sanduku@nr.usu.edu">Paul Box</ulink>)</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </simplesect>

  <simplesect id="release-savannah">
    <title>Savannah site</title> 
    
    <para>Swarm is in the process of migrating it's <ulink
      url="http://sourceforge.net/projects/swarm/">SourceForge
      presence</ulink> to the <ulink
      url="http://savannah.gnu.org/">Savannah</ulink> development site
      run by the <ulink url="http://www.gnu.org/">Free Software
      Foundation</ulink> for hosting free software projects.</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para><ulink
        url="http://savannah.gnu.org/projects/swarm">http://savannah.gnu.org/projects/swarm/</ulink></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>The latest source tarballs for Swarm and swarmapps will be
      made available there, so it acts as a partial mirror if you
      can't access <literal>ftp.swarm.org</literal> or one of the
      other mirrors.  In the future, we plan to use some of Savannah's
      features for co-ordinating projects and/or allow users to
      co-ordinate their own Swarm-related projects.</para>

    <para>Several users are already using SourceForge for
      co-ordinating their projects, these are independent from the
      SDG:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Artificial Stock Market:  <ulink url="http://sourceforge.net/projects/artstkmkt">http://sourceforge.net/projects/artstkmkt/</ulink></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Evo: <ulink url="http://sourceforge.net/projects/evo">http://sourceforge.net/projects/evo/</ulink></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

  </simplesect>

  <simplesect id="release-cdrom">
    <title>Swarm CD-ROM currently unavailable</title>

    <para>The Swarm 2.1.1 CD-ROM is currently unavailable.  However,
    should a future Swarm CD-ROM become available (no release date has
    be set, nor can we promise that there will be such a release) it
    will be announced on <literal>swarm-announce</literal> mailing
    list, to which you can <link
    linkend="community-mailing-lists">subscribe</link>. </para>

